try {
  const rubric = {
    appointment_conversion: { weight: 0.30, description: 'Did the agent successfully guide toward booking?' },
    objection_handling:     { weight: 0.25, description: 'Did the agent address concerns effectively?' },
    conversation_flow:      { weight: 0.15, description: 'Natural pacing, one question at a time, appropriate pauses' },
    information_accuracy:   { weight: 0.15, description: 'Did the agent provide correct practice information?' },
    rapport_building:       { weight: 0.10, description: 'Did the agent build trust and show empathy?' },
    compliance:             { weight: 0.05, description: 'No medical advice, no fabricated availability, proper boundaries' }
  };

  // current_prompt, prompt_version, prior_scores, changelog_history are injected by server.py
  const currentPrompt = $json.current_prompt || 'Prompt unavailable — evaluate from call data only.';
  const priorScores = $json.prior_scores || [];
  const changelogHistory = $json.changelog_history || [];
  const toolCalls = $json.tool_calls || [];

  console.log('[Code Prepare Inputs] prompt_version:', $json.prompt_version, 'prior_scores:', priorScores.length, 'tool_calls:', toolCalls.length);

  return [{ json: {
    call: $json,
    current_prompt: currentPrompt,
    prior_scores: priorScores,
    changelog_history: changelogHistory,
    tool_calls: toolCalls,
    rubric
  }}];
} catch (error) {
  return [{ json: { error: String(error), raw_call: $json } }];
}

parameters.jsonBody:
={{ {
  system_instruction: {
    parts: [{
      text: `You are an expert call center quality analyst evaluating AI voice agent performance.

SCORING ANCHORS — use these exact criteria, not your own interpretation:
appointment_conversion: 5=Appointment booked with full confirmation, 4=Strong attempt/callback scheduled, 3=Partial progress/interest maintained, 2=Missed clear booking opportunity, 1=Caller lost interest due to agent behavior
objection_handling: 5=All objections addressed with empathy and resolution, 4=Most handled/minor misses, 3=Basic handling/lacked depth, 2=Fumbled primary objection, 1=Ignored or argued with caller concern
conversation_flow: 5=Flowed like natural phone conversation, 4=Mostly natural/minor awkward transitions, 3=Some robotic patterns or stacked questions, 2=Frequently unnatural/multiple stacked questions, 1=Completely scripted feel
information_accuracy: 5=All information accurate and relevant, 4=Accurate with minor omissions, 3=Mostly accurate/one notable error, 2=Multiple inaccuracies, 1=Fabricated information or hallucinated details
rapport_building: 5=Warm/empathetic/caller felt heard, 4=Friendly and professional, 3=Polite but impersonal, 2=Cold or transactional, 1=Rude/dismissive/argumentative
compliance: 5=Perfect boundary maintenance, 4=Minor softness/no harm, 3=Came close to overstepping once, 2=Provided quasi-medical guidance, 1=Gave medical advice or fabricated data

RULES:
1. For any score below 4, you MUST quote the exact transcript moment that justifies the deduction
2. If outcome is DROPPED or DECLINED and transcript has fewer than 2 user turns, score appointment_conversion as 1 and focus scoring on engagement/rapport/first-impression
3. If tool_calls is provided, evaluate whether the agent used check_availability and show_confirmation correctly — failure to use them when needed is an information_accuracy deduction
4. If prior_scores is provided, note any dimension that has regressed from the previous version
5. Output structured JSON ONLY, no other text`
    }]
  },
  contents: [{
    role: 'user',
    parts: [{
      text: `CALL DATA:
${JSON.stringify($json.call, null, 2)}

CURRENT PROMPT:
${$json.current_prompt}

TOOL CALLS MADE:
${JSON.stringify($json.tool_calls || [], null, 2)}

PRIOR SCORES (most recent first):
${JSON.stringify($json.prior_scores || [], null, 2)}

RUBRIC:
${JSON.stringify($json.rubric, null, 2)}

Return JSON with keys: scores (object with each dimension name -> {score, justification, evidence_quote}), weighted_total, top_failure_points (array of {moment, problem, fix}), strengths_to_preserve (array of strings), prompt_fix_suggestions (array of strings), regression_flags (array of dimension names that scored lower than prior version, or empty array).`
    }]
  }]
} }}

